<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="583" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1087,1150]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">
This is a very large trichopteran family in the Neotropics, with five genera and over 277 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R." pageId="5" pageNumber="583" pagination="1 - 566" refId="ref5887" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R. (2017) Catalog of the Neotropical Trichoptera (Caddisflies). Zookeys, 654, 1 - 566. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 654.9516" type="journal article" year="2017">Holzenthal &amp; Calor 2017</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[261,353,1124,1150]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">Panama</collectingCountry>
, three genera are recorded: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[662,772,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Chimarra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[662,772,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">Chimarra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lestage" authorityYear="1925" box="[786,966,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Chimarrhodella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[786,966,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">Chimarrhodella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1865" box="[1028,1151,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Wormaldia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1028,1151,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">Wormaldia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
